page.title: 20PUBLIC TRANSPORT
page.content: If you would like to go from Woking to Waterloo in the morning, you could get the 07:56 train which arrives at Waterloo at 08:22. It costs Â£2 to Â£3 for the train journey. If you would have to go by your ticket at the booking office, and then show the inspector your ticket at the gate to the platform. Some trains stop at different stations on the way. For instance, Weybridge, Wimbledon and Surbiton. On some trains lunch is avalible. Other trains travel fast and do not stop until they are in London. Some trains are called INTER-CITY. Buses.
